column4: Iridium says last call from its device on missing Argentine submarine was Wednesday
column5: BUENOS AIRES U.S. satellite communications company Iridium Communications Inc  said on Sunday the last call from its device aboard a missing Argentine submarine was made at 1136 GMT on Wednesday   the day the vessel vanished.

column4: Airbus faces tricky hurdles over stalled A380 Emirates deal

column4: Avolon agrees to buy 75 Boeing aircraft  may order 20 more
column5: HONG KONG  Nov 19 Chinese aircraft leasing company Bohai Capital said on Sunday its Avolon Aerospace Leasing Ltd subsidiary had agreed to buy 55 B737 MAX 8 and 20 B737 MAX 10 aircraft from Boeing  and may order an additional 20 M737 MAX 8  with a total list value of around $11 billion.
